    <statement><p>Calculate the following. Use an improper fraction in your answer.</p>
<p><ol label="a.">
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{ \frac{25}{8} }{ \frac{5}{9} } =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\frac{ \frac{t}{r} }{ \frac{y}{x} } =}</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0002"/></p>
</li>
</ol></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{45}{8}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{tx}{ry}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><alert>Problem 1</alert></p>
<p>To simplify a complex fraction, we find the common denominator of all fractions. In this case, it is <m>72</m>. We multiply the complex fraction<rsq/>s numerator and denominator by this common denominator, and we have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    
      \amp = \frac{ \frac{25}{8} \cdot 72 }{ \frac{5}{9} \cdot 72 } \\
      \amp = \frac{ 225 }{ 40 } \\
      \amp = {{\frac{45}{8}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Here is a simple way to do fraction multiplication:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ \frac{25}{8} \cdot 72 = 72 \div 8 \cdot 25 = 225 }</m></p>
<p><alert>Problem 2</alert></p>
<p>To simplify a complex fraction, we find the common denominator of all fractions. In this case, it is <m>{rx}</m>. We multiply the complex fraction<rsq/>s numerator and denominator by this common denominator, and we have:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
    
      \amp = \frac{ \frac{t}{r} \cdot {rx} }{ \frac{y}{x} \cdot {rx} } \\
      \amp = {\frac{tx}{ry}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
</solution>
